<h4></h4>
<h4>Release Notes</h4>
<ul>
 	<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
 	<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Version</strong>: v4.2.0</li>
 	<li><strong>Date</strong>: 2017-Mar-30</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h5>New Features</h5>
<ul class="clList labelList">
 	<li><span class="targetLabel common">All</span>
<ul>
 	<li>Supported products in a series with HIVE IAP v2.</li>
 	<li>Improved implementation method of Auth (Engagement).</li>
 	<li>Added API:
<ul>
 	<li>Added the feature of PlatformHelper.
<ul>
 	<li>Supported the general use of UA Share feature.</li>
 	<li>PlatformHelper.shareText(…)</li>
 	<li>PlatformHelper.shareMedia(…)</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li>Added SocialHive - getProfiles() API.
<ul>
 	<li>Obtained the HIVE user lists through vid lists of each user.</li>
 	<li>SociHive.getProfiles(vidList[] , Callback)</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li>Added SocialFacebook - isLogin() API.
<ul>
 	<li>Returned the login status by checking whether the current value of Facebook AccessToken exists.</li>
 	<li>boolean SocialFacebook.isLogin()</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li>Added Auth - setEngagementReady() API (Modifying significant operation).
<ul>
 	<li>Processed EngagementEvent which immediately runs through login after sending Ready signal from Application.</li>
 	<li>boolean Auth.setEngagementReady(boolean isReady)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h5>Changed Features</h5>
<ul class="clList labelList">
 	<li><span class="targetLabel common">All</span>
<ul>
 	<li>[IAP] Changed the result callback of Purchase and Restore.
<ul>
 	<li>AS-IS
1) onIAPPurchase(ResultAPI result)
2) onIAPRestore(ResultAPI result)</li>
 	<li>TO-BE
1) onIAPPurchase(ResultAPI result, Product product, String iapTransactionId)
2) onIAPRestore(ResultAPI result, Product[] product, String[] iapTransactionId)</li>
 	<li>Remarks
1) Send the payment ID as well as product information after purchase success.
2) Send the payment ID as well as product information in an array after restoring the purchase list.</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li>[IAP] Changes in product model:
<ul>
 	<li>Added product data in a series.
[Field Added]
salesStartUTC (long): The time product is valid. Unlimited if it is -1.
salesExpireUTC (long): The time product is expired. Unlimited if it is -1.
productType (string): The type of product: general (General product), series (Series product)
SeriesInfo (inner class): Series product data, The field does not exist unless series product.
seriesSeq (int): The order of product in a series.
seriesTotalCount (int): The number of product in a series.
seriesPurchaseStatus (int): 1: Before purchase, 2: Purchase complete.
request_type (int): 1: Purchase, 2: Restore.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h5>Bug Fixes</h5>
<ul class="clList labelList">
 	<li><span class="targetLabel common">All</span>
<ul>
 	<li>Fixed to display Facebook login button when executing HiveLogin.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul class="clList labelList">
 	<li><span class="targetLabel android">Android </span>
<ul>
 	<li>[Engagement] Fixed the network error for using coupons.</li>
 	<li>Fixed to read the correct settings for display in Chinese (Simplified, Traditional) from the default value (English).</li>
 	<li>Fixed to display Back button on Notice Popup, Promotion Banner and End/Review Popup. (HotFix 4.1.2)</li>
 	<li>Fixed the crash with API Level 25 (7.1). (HotFix 4.1.1)</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li><span class="targetLabel iOS">iOS </span>
<ul>
 	<li>[IAP] Fixed the freezing purchase status when IAP server failed to respond in the middle of purchase process with HIVE IAP.</li>
 	<li>[SocialHive] Fixed the crash when using the gallery feature on iPad. (HotFix 4.1.3)</li>
 	<li>[SocialHive] Fixed the crash after user denies or accepts the request from HIVE to access the camera function. (HotFix 4.1.3)</li>
 	<li>[Auth] Added GNB (Back to Game) button on the Select UI. (HotFix 4.1.3)</li>
 	<li>[IAP] Fixed the errors with purchase restoring logic when forced termination or other features run in the middle of purchase process. (HotFix 4.1.3)</li>
 	<li>[Promotion] Fixed the BannerType Orientation determination logic. (HotFix 4.1.3)</li>
